{{農業和農學}}

[[File:Slashing-and-burning.jpg|thumb]]
[[File:An_example_of_slash_and_burn_agriculture_practice_Thailand.jpg|缩略图]]
[[File:Kaskialue_Kaavin_Telkkämäessä_(2013).JPG|缩略图]]

'''刀耕火種'''，或稱'''刀耕火耨'''、'''火耕'''，是一種以砍伐及焚燒林地上的植物來獲得耕地的古老農業技術<ref name="bbc@20130624">{{Cite web |url = https://www.bbc.com/news/business-23026219 |title = South East Asia haze: What is slash-and-burn? |author = BBC |date = 2013-06-24 |publisher = BBC |language = en |accessdate = 2019-07-08 |archive-date = 2020-12-14 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201214025922/https://www.bbc.com/news/business-23026219 |dead-url = no }}</ref>。農民首先會砍伐一個地區的[[樹木|樹木]]及[[木本植物|木本植物]]，待樹木乾燥後再作焚燒，此舉所產生的富含營養的[[草木灰|草木灰]]能使土壤肥沃，土壤的生產力亦暫時性得以提升<ref name="bbc@20130624"/>。在經過數年的耕作後，耕地會因養分大量流失而變得貧瘠，農民便會棄置現有耕地並另闢新的耕地<ref name="bbc@20130624"/><ref name="Tschakert et al,. 2007">{{Cite journal|author= Petra Tschakert |author2= Oliver T.Coomes |author3= Catherine Potvin |title= Indigenous livelihoods, slash-and-burn agriculture, and carbon stocks in Eastern Panama |journal= Ecological Economics |year= 2007 |volume= 60 |issue= 4 |pages= 807-820}}</ref><ref name="rainforest saver">{{Cite web |url = https://www.rainforestsaver.org/what-slash-and-burn-farming |title = What is slash and burn farming? |author = Rainforest Saver |date = 2019-06-28 |language = en |accessdate = 2019-07-08 |archive-date = 2020-12-14 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201214025932/https://www.rainforestsaver.org/what-slash-and-burn-farming |dead-url = no }}</ref>。在印度，這種農業技術被稱為「jhum」<ref>{{Cite journal|author= Sanjoy Choudhury |title= Jhum |journal= Geography and You |year= 2010 |volume= 10 |issue= 59}}</ref>或「jhoom」<ref>{{Cite book | author = Disha Experts | title = 1500+ MCQs with Explanatory Notes For GEOGRAPHY, ECOLOGY & ENVIRONMENT | publisher = Disha Publications | date = 2018 | accessdate = 2019-07-08 | language = en}} </ref>。而在[[瑪雅文明|瑪雅文明]]中，有一種類似的技術被稱為「米爾帕（Milpa）」<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.redalyc.org/jatsRepo/104/10454952011/html/index.html |title = Effects of Slash-and-Burn-Farming and a Fire-Free Management on a Cambisol in a Traditional Maya Farming System |author = Roland Ebel |date = 2017-07-04 |publisher = Redalyc |language = en |accessdate = 2019-07-12 |archive-date = 2020-08-20 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200820122407/https://www.redalyc.org/jatsRepo/104/10454952011/html/index.html |dead-url = no }}</ref>。

此種農業技術對於人口增長迅速的現代世界來說不具備可擴展性及[[可持續性|可持續性]]<ref name="Brady, 1996">{{Cite journal |author= Nyle C.Brady |title= Alternatives to slash-and-burn: a global imperative |url= https://archive.org/details/sim_agriculture-ecosystems-environment_1996-06_58_1/page/n10 |journal= Agriculture, Ecosystems & Environment |year= 1996 |volume= 58 |issue= 1 |pages= 3-11}}</ref><ref name="Bandy, 1994">{{Cite web |url = https://www.worldagroforestry.org/Units/Library/Books/PDFs/75_Alternatives_to_slash-and-burn.pdf |title = Alternatives to slash-and-burn. A global strategy |author = Dale Bandy |year = 1994 |publisher = International Center for Research in Agroforestry |language = en |accessdate = 2019-07-10 |archive-date = 2019-07-10 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190710141825/https://www.worldagroforestry.org/Units/Library/Books/PDFs/75_Alternatives_to_slash-and-burn.pdf |dead-url = no }}</ref>。儘管如此，經粗略估計全世界仍然有7%的人口（約2億至5億人）使用此技術開闢新的耕地<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.nasa.gov/image-feature/goddard/2016/first-comes-fire-then-comes-crops-in-india |title = First Comes Fire Then Comes Crops in India |author = Lynn Jenner |date = 2016-03-23 |publisher = NASA |language = en |accessdate = 2019-07-09 |archive-date = 2020-11-08 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201108112656/http://www.nasa.gov/image-feature/goddard/2016/first-comes-fire-then-comes-crops-in-india/ |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |author = Ishan Y Pandya, Harshad D. Salvi |title = Significance of Tropical Woods of Southern Gujarat |location = Raleigh, NC |publisher = Lulu Publication |date = 2017 |pages = 206 |ISBN = 978-1-387-21570-6 |accessdate = 2019-07-09 |language = en}}</ref>。

== 歷史 ==
世界大部分地區都有著農民使用刀耕火種開闢耕地的歷史。在[[新石器革命|新石器革命]]時，人類開始由[[狩獵採集|狩獵採集]]社會轉型至農耕社會，但隨著人口增加，食物的需求亦漸漸增加，因此耕地變得重要。為了獲得更多的耕地，人們開始利用刀耕火種這種技術來清除更多的土地，以供種植及放牧。因此，自新石器時代以來，刀耕火種這種技術已被人類廣泛用於將林地轉變為農田和牧場<ref>{{Cite book |author = Jaime Awe |title = Maya Cities and Sacred Caves: A Guide to the Maya Sites of Belize |location = Benque Viejo del Carmen, Belize |publisher = Cubola Productions |date = 2006 |accessdate = 2019-07-10 |language = en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.odi.org/sites/odi.org.uk/files/odi-assets/publications-opinion-files/1162.pdf |title = Slash-and-Burn in the Historyof the Swedish Forests |author = Henning Hamilton |date = 1997 |publisher = Rural Development Forestry Network |language = en |accessdate = 2019-07-10 |archive-date = 2020-08-20 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200820125506/https://www.odi.org/sites/odi.org.uk/files/odi-assets/publications-opinion-files/1162.pdf |dead-url = no }}</ref>。由於當時的人口對土地的壓力較低，而且人們的生計以[[自給農業|自給農業]]為主，因此這種技術在那段時期是很有效的<ref name="Chhetri et al., 2018">{{Cite journal|author= Raju Chhetri |author2= Pramod Prasad Dahal |author3= Kalpana Pokhrel |author4= Bishnu Maharjan |author5= Saurav Suman |title= “Expedition From Slash And Burn To Agroforestry Plantation, A Livelihood Upliftment Subsequences Of “Bankariya Ethnics”:A Case Study Of „Manahari Rural Municipality‟ Within Central Nepal. |journal= International Journal of Humanities and Social Science Invention |year= 2018 |volume= 7 |issue= 7 |pages= 1-9}}</ref>。在歷史上，居於歐洲、西非及南美洲等地的農民均有使用刀耕火種的紀錄<ref name="Wickel, 2004">{{Cite book |author = Bart Wickel |title = Water and Nutrient Dynamics of a Humid Tropical Agricultural Watershed in Eastern Amazonia |location = Göttingen, Germany |publisher = Cuvillier Verlag |date = 2004 |accessdate = 2019-07-12 |language = en}}</ref><ref name="North Dakota State University, 2001">{{Cite web |url = https://core.ac.uk/download/pdf/6813661.pdf |title = Farmer Education and Adoption of Slash and Burn Agriculture |author = William Nganje, Eric C. Schuck, Debazou Yantio, Emmanuel Aquach |date = 2001 |publisher = North Dakota State University, Department of Agribusiness and Applied Economics |language = en |accessdate = 2019-07-13 |archive-date = 2020-08-20 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200820120021/https://core.ac.uk/download/pdf/6813661.pdf |dead-url = no }}</ref>。另外在唐宋時期，部分農業民族例如[[畲族|畲族]]、[[苗族|苗族]]、[[瑤族|瑤族]]、[[壯族|壯族]]等都主要以刀耕火種為主要特徵<ref>{{Cite journal |author= 曾雄生 |title= 唐宋時期的畬田與畬田民族的歷史走向 |journal= 古今農業 |year= 2005 |issue= 4 |pages= 30-41}}</ref>。

在19世纪和20世纪初，刀耕火種對一些人口较為稀疏的地区來說是一种可持续的技术，因為耕地有足夠時間恢復營養。但隨著世界人口爆增，輪耕的周期不斷加快，農民不得不將森林開闢為新的耕地，以致[[森林砍伐|森林砍伐]]的問題日益惡化<ref name="Tschakert et al,. 2007"/><ref name="Bandy, 1994"/>。

== 應用 ==
刀耕火種是一种在[[自給農業|自給農業]]中经常使用的技术，除了開闢耕地外，農民還會使用此技術用以開闢畜牧場。在[[旱季|旱季]]時，農民會利用斧頭及镰刀等工具砍伐林地上的樹木及木本植物，當植物乾枯一段時間，農民便會在中午時份焚燒乾枯的植物，而植物經焚燒後所產生的富含營養的[[草木灰|草木灰]]則能使土壤變得肥沃<ref name="Wickel, 2004"/><ref name="Cochrane, 2010">{{Cite book |author = Mark Cochrane |title = Tropical Fire Ecology: Climate Change, Land Use and Ecosystem Dynamics |location = New York, USA |publisher = Springer Science & Business Media |date = 2010 |ISBN = 978-3-540-77380-1 |accessdate = 2019-07-12 |language = en}}</ref><ref name="Mazoyer and Roudart, 2006">{{Cite book |author = Marcel Mazoyer, Laurence Roudart |title = A History of World Agriculture: From the Neolithic Age to the Current Crisis |location = London, UK |publisher = Earthscan |date = 2006 |ISBN = 978-1-84407-399-3 |accessdate = 2019-07-12 |language = en}}</ref><ref name="Challen, 2005">{{Cite book |author = Paul Clarence Challen |title = Environmental Disaster Alert! |url = https://archive.org/details/environmentaldis0000chal |publisher = Crabtree Publishing Company |date = 2005 |ISBN = 978-0-77871-581-8 |accessdate = 2019-07-12 |language = en}}</ref>。

刀耕火種的穩定性大多取決於整個生態系統的總營養成分，而不是刀耕火種後土壤的淨增益<ref name="Juo and Manu, 1996">{{Cite journal |author1= Anthony S.R. Juo |author2= Andrew Manu |title= Chemical dynamics in slash-and-burn agriculture |url= https://archive.org/details/sim_agriculture-ecosystems-environment_1996-06_58_1/page/49 |journal= Agriculture, Ecosystems & Environment |year= 1996 |volume= 58 |issue= 1 |pages= 49-60}}</ref>。在土地開發的第一個週期中，刀耕火種將大量儲存在地上[[生物量|生物量]]中的營養物質釋放到土壤中<ref name="Juo and Manu, 1996"/>。因此，土壤中營養物質的增加是以植物生物量為代價<ref name="Juo and Manu, 1996"/>。儘管在刀耕火種後土壤的養分供應會短期增加，但另一方面，在焚燒林木期間大部分的礦物營養素可能會因為[[侵蝕作用|侵蝕作用]]或[[淋溶作用|淋溶作用]]而流失，例如鉀、鎂、鈣、硝酸鹽及硫酸鹽等<ref name="Juo and Manu, 1996"/><ref name="Giardina et al., 2000">{{Cite journal |author= Christian P. Giardina |author2= Robert L. Sanford |author3= Ingrid C. Døckersmith |author4= Victor J. Jaramillo |title= The effects of slash burning on ecosystem nutrients during the land preparation phase of shifting cultivation |url= https://archive.org/details/sim_plant-and-soil_2000_220_1-2/page/247 |journal= Plant and Soil |year= 2000 |volume= 220 |issue= 1-2 |pages= 247-260}}</ref>。另一方面土壤內的營養物質會因被作物吸收而減少，故整個生態系統中的總營養數量會逐漸減少<ref name="Juo and Manu, 1996"/><ref name="Giardina et al., 2000"/>。當土地變得貧瘠，農民便會利用同樣技術清除林地並開闢新的耕地<ref name="Cochrane, 2010"/><ref name="Mazoyer and Roudart, 2006"/>。由於農民經常從一個耕地轉移到另一個耕地，因此刀耕火種可被視為[[輪耕|輪耕]]的其中一種方式<ref name="Ramakrishnan and Patnaik, 1992">{{Cite journal|author= P. S. Ramakrishnan |author2= Suprava Patnaik |title= Jhum: Slash and Burn Cultivation |journal= India International Centre Quarterly |year= 1992 |volume= 19 |issue= 1/2 |pages= 215-220}}</ref>。

在[[巴西|巴西]]，儘管清除森林是非法的，大量農民仍然使用刀耕火種在亞馬遜森林內開闢耕地，並種植[[經濟作物|經濟作物]]如大豆及玉米等<ref name="Watts, 2012">{{Cite web |url = https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2012/nov/14/brazil-amazon-rangers-farmers-burning |title = Brazil's Amazon rangers battle farmers' burning business logic |author = Jonathan Watts |date = 2012-11-14 |publisher = The Guardian |language = en |accessdate = 2019-07-13 |archive-date = 2020-12-14 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201214030013/https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2012/nov/14/brazil-amazon-rangers-farmers-burning |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="Branford, 2017">{{Cite web |url = https://www.ft.com/content/9c750b08-92f0-11e7-83ab-f4624cccbabe |title = A fight for Brazil’s Amazon forest |author = Sue Branford |date = 2017-09-20 |publisher = The Financial Times |language = en |accessdate = 2019-07-13 |archive-date = 2020-12-14 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201214030004/https://www.ft.com/content/9c750b08-92f0-11e7-83ab-f4624cccbabe |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="Darlington, 2012">{{Cite web |url = https://edition.cnn.com/2012/03/18/world/americas/eco-brazil-forest-code/index.html |title = Brazil tries to balance farming and forests |author = Shasta Darlington |date = 2012-03-19 |publisher = CNN |language = en |accessdate = 2019-07-13 |archive-date = 2020-12-14 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201214030038/https://edition.cnn.com/2012/03/18/world/americas/eco-brazil-forest-code/index.html |dead-url = no }}</ref>。而在[[印度尼西亞|印度尼西亞]]，大部份的小農使用刀耕火種來清除熱帶雨林，以便開發棕櫚油種植園<ref name="Arshad, 2016">{{Cite web |url = https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/se-asia/firms-pay-farmers-to-be-slash-and-burn-fall-guys |title = Indonesian firms pay farmers to be slash-and-burn 'fall guys' |author = Arlina Arshad |date = 2016-09-11 |publisher = The Straits Times |language = en |accessdate = 2019-07-14 |archive-date = 2020-12-14 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201214030016/https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/se-asia/firms-pay-farmers-to-be-slash-and-burn-fall-guys |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="Schecter, 2015">{{Cite web |url = https://www.devex.com/news/slash-and-burn-in-indonesia-getting-to-the-root-of-the-problem-87295 |title = 'Slash and burn' in Indonesia: Getting to the root of the problem |author = Kate Schecter |date = 2015-11-30 |publisher = Devex |language = en |accessdate = 2019-07-14 |archive-date = 2020-12-14 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201214030019/https://www.devex.com/news/slash-and-burn-in-indonesia-getting-to-the-root-of-the-problem-87295 |dead-url = no }}</ref>。另外，部份農業企業更會向一些居於貧困村落的農民支付金錢，要求他們清理他們的耕地以供種植棕櫚樹及生產紙漿，而農民在收取金錢後便會使用刀耕火種來清理耕地<ref name="Arshad, 2016"/><ref name="Schecter, 2015"/>。

== 影響 ==
{{Further|{{link-en|1997年印尼森林大火|1997 Indonesian forest fires}}|2006年東南亞霾害|2013年東南亞霾害|2015年东南亚霾害|2019年亞馬遜雨林野火}}

在印尼[[蘇門答臘|蘇門答臘]]和[[加里曼丹|加里曼丹]]等地，由於大部份農民習慣使用刀耕火種技術清理土地，以種植棕櫚樹及生產紙漿，因此森林大火及其衍生的霾害問題每年都會發生<ref name="端傳媒@2016">{{Cite web |url = https://theinitium.com/article/20160919-dailynews-indonesia-toxic-haze/ |title = 印尼森林大火後患無窮，研究指霾害致10萬人早死 |author = 端傳媒 |date = 2016-09-20 |language = zh |accessdate = 2019-07-14 |archive-date = 2020-12-14 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201214030054/https://theinitium.com/article/20160919-dailynews-indonesia-toxic-haze/ |dead-url = no }}</ref>。環保組織[[綠色和平|綠色和平]]指出印尼境內的雨林在過去數十年已經有超過四份之一被毀，更將矛頭指向棕櫚油企業及一些棕櫚油消費品牌<ref>{{Cite web |url = http://www.greenpeace.org/hk/news/stories/forests/2016/03/who-still-burning-indonesia-forests/ |title = 誰仍在火燒印尼雨林？ |author = 綠色和平 |date = 2016-03-04 |language = zh |accessdate = 2019-07-14 |archive-date = 2019-06-10 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190610153509/http://www.greenpeace.org/hk/news/stories/forests/2016/03/who-still-burning-indonesia-forests/ |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="綠色和平@2017">{{Cite web |url = http://www.greenpeace.org/hk/news/stories/forests/2017/01/IOI-palm-oil/ |title = 不可挽回的破壞 — 印尼雨林的無聲吶喊 |author = 綠色和平 |date = 2017-01-09 |language = zh |accessdate = 2019-07-14 |archive-date = 2019-07-03 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190703235635/http://www.greenpeace.org/hk/news/stories/forests/2017/01/IOI-palm-oil/ |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="Gould, 2016">{{Cite web |url = https://www.theguardian.com/sustainable-business/2016/jun/09/palm-oil-giant-ioi-impact-indonesia-worse-than-reported-says-greenpeace |title = Palm oil giant's impact in Indonesia worse than reported, says Greenpeace |author = Hannah Gould |date = 2016-06-09 |publisher = The Guardian |language = en |accessdate = 2019-07-14 |archive-date = 2020-12-14 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201214030053/https://www.theguardian.com/sustainable-business/2016/jun/09/palm-oil-giant-ioi-impact-indonesia-worse-than-reported-says-greenpeace |dead-url = no }}</ref>。在2015年11月，綠色和平發現婆羅洲某一地區出現了災情嚴重的火災，更在數個月後變成了[[油棕|油棕]]種植園<ref name="綠色和平@2017"/>。他們指此舉不但摧毀寶貴的熱帶雨林，更會趕絕棲息其中的雨林動物，如[[紅毛猩猩|紅毛猩猩]]、[[長鼻猴|長鼻猴]]及[[馬來熊|馬來熊]]<ref name="綠色和平@2017"/><ref name="Gould, 2016"/>。另外在2015年6月，由於非法的刀耕火種活動而導致印尼出現山火，其後更引起嚴重霧霾，並波及新加坡、馬來西亞等國<ref name="端傳媒@2016"/>。有研究指出在2015年該地區排放了8.84億噸二氧化碳，其中97％來自印尼的山火，更表示二氧化碳排放量相較1997年的火災更嚴重<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/se-asia/indonesia-forest-fires-in-2015-released-most-carbon-since-1997-scientists |title = Indonesia forest fires in 2015 released most carbon since 1997: Scientists |author = Thomson Reuters Foundation |date = 2016-06-29 |publisher = The Straits Times |language = en |accessdate = 2019-07-14 |archive-date = 2020-12-14 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201214030115/https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/se-asia/indonesia-forest-fires-in-2015-released-most-carbon-since-1997-scientists |dead-url = no }}</ref>。另一方面，有研究推算印尼、新加坡及馬來西亞三國共有10.03萬人因為2015年印尼森林大火而過早死亡<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/sep/19/haze-indonesia-forest-fires-killed-100000-people-harvard-study |title = Haze from Indonesian fires may have killed more than 100,000 people – study |author = Agence France-Presse |date = 2016-09-19 |publisher = The Guardian |language = en |accessdate = 2019-07-14 |archive-date = 2020-12-14 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201214030124/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/sep/19/haze-indonesia-forest-fires-killed-100000-people-harvard-study |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |author= Shannon N Koplitz1 |author2= Loretta J Mickley |author3= Miriam E Marlier |author4= Jonathan J Buonocore |author5= Patrick S Kim1 |author6= Tianjia Liu |author7= Melissa P Sulprizio |author8= Ruth S DeFries |author9= Daniel J Jacob1 |author10= Joel Schwartz |author11= Montira Pongsiri |author12= Samuel S Myers |title= Public health impacts of the severe haze in Equatorial Asia in September–October 2015: demonstration of a new framework for informing fire management strategies to reduce downwind smoke exposure |journal= Environmental Research Letters |year= 2016 |volume= 11 |issue= 9}}</ref>。

在巴西，有報道指出截至2017年9月發生於亞馬遜地區的[[帕拉州|帕拉州]]的火災相較2016年增加了229%<ref name="Sullivan, 2018">{{Cite web |url = https://news.mongabay.com/2018/01/record-amazon-fires-intensified-by-forest-degradation-burn-indigenous-lands/ |title = Record Amazon fires, intensified by forest degradation, burn indigenous lands |author = Zoe Sullivan |date = 2018-01-18 |publisher = Mongabay |language = en |accessdate = 2019-07-14 |archive-date = 2020-12-20 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201220060544/https://news.mongabay.com/2018/01/record-amazon-fires-intensified-by-forest-degradation-burn-indigenous-lands/ |dead-url = no }}</ref>。研究人員指出大多數的山火都是人為造成的，原因是人們清除森林並將林地轉化為耕地，而採礦公司、伐木企業和農業綜合企業則加劇了[[森林退化|森林退化]]問題<ref name="Sullivan, 2018"/>。儘管森林法規禁止任何人在[[大西洋沿岸森林|大西洋沿岸森林]]進行刀耕火種，但破壞仍然存在<ref name="Nuwer, 2012">{{Cite web |url = https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2012/08/years-after-slash-and-burn-brazil-haunted-black-carbon |title = Years After Slash and Burn, Brazil Haunted by 'Black Carbon' |author = Rachel Nuwer |date = 2012-08-12 |publisher = American Association for the Advancement of Science |language = en |accessdate = 2019-07-15 |archive-date = 2020-12-14 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201214030146/https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2012/08/years-after-slash-and-burn-brazil-haunted-black-carbon |dead-url = no }}</ref>。有研究指出植物在被焚燒後所產生的殘留物會因[[淋溶作用|淋溶作用]]而流入河流並最終進入海洋，而這種被稱為「黑碳（Black carbon）」的物質在進入海洋生態系統後更可能會傷害海洋生物<ref name="Dittmar et al., 2012">{{Cite journal |author= Thorsten Dittmar |author2= Carlos Eduardo de Rezende |author3= Marcus Manecki |author4= Marcus Manecki |author5= Jutta Niggemann |author6= Alvaro Ramon Coelho Ovalle |author7= Aron Stubbins |author8= Marcelo Correa Bernardes |title= Continuous flux of dissolved black carbon from a vanished tropical forest biome |journal= Nature Geoscience |year= 2012 |volume= 5 |pages= 618-622}}</ref>。

